Name:          Ada Lovelace
Lived:         1815 - 1852
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     First computer algorithm
Contribution:  Wrote first algorithm for Babbage's machine; recognized computing potential
Quote:         "The Analytical Engine weaves algebraic patterns."

Name:          Florence Nightingale
Lived:         1820 - 1910
Nationality:   English
Field:         Medicine
Known For:     Modern nursing
Contribution:  Founded modern nursing; used statistics; reduced Crimean War mortality 40% to 2%
Quote:         "I attribute my success to this: I never gave or took any excuse."

Name:          Mahatma Gandhi
Lived:         1869 - 1948
Nationality:   Indian
Field:         Politics
Known For:     Non-violent independence movement
Contribution:  Led India to independence; satyagraha philosophy; influenced MLK and Mandela
Quote:         "Be the change you wish to see in the world."

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Plato's Theory of Forms
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Physical objects are imperfect copies of eternal abstract Forms
Philosopher:  Plato
Example:      The perfect circle exists only as a Form; drawn circles approximate it

Concept:      Existentialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Existence precedes essence; radical freedom and responsibility
Philosopher:  Jean-Paul Sartre
Example:      You are not born kind or cruel; you become so through choices

Concept:      Dialectical Materialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   History driven by material economic forces through thesis-antithesis-synthesis
Philosopher:  Karl Marx/Hegel
Example:      Class struggle between bourgeoisie and proletariat drives history

